20/08/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Alfred Paloka, former Democratic Party (DP) lawmaker and current director of the Albanian Telegraphic Agency, will be the DP's candidate in the special election called to fill a seat in parliament. It was left vacant after Bamir Topi became president. The election is scheduled for September 20th. Dashamir Shehi, head of the National Development Movement, is the only other candidate in the race so far. (Shekulli, Kohajone - 19/08/07; Balkanweb - 18/08/07)
